    "TF-IDF (Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency) Soft Deduping (Chen et al, 2023c).",
    "This method involves calculating the TF-IDF weight of each word in the text to compare the similarity between texts.",
    "Texts with similarity above a threshold are deleted.",
    "TF-IDF weight is the frequency of a word in the text (TF) multiplied by the inverse document frequency (IDF) across the entire corpus.",
    "Higher weights indicate that a word frequently appears in a particular text but is uncommon across the entire corpus, making it a key feature of the text."
